overview: The user aimed to enhance a sleep questionnaire application by adding
  a database for response storage, an admin dashboard for data access, and an
  authentication system. I developed a plan that included updating demographics,
  creating a Prisma QuestionnaireResponse model, implementing API routes for
  data handling (save, retrieve, CSV export), and building a simple admin
  dashboard. The authentication system was initially designed with custom
  session management but was later refined to leverage Next.js middleware for a
  more streamlined and efficient approach to route protection. While the
  database setup and admin dashboard functionality were successfully implemented
  and verified, the conversation concluded with an unresolved issue regarding
  the questionnaire form's submission to the database during testing, suggesting
  a potential validation or submission logic problem.
